el_questionnaire.1.player.reasons_belief: I roughly guessed the odds that they chose X given a success or failure, but was swayed a few percentages if the investment payoff was low, suspecting that the leader would be more inclined to take the safe money.  I am beginning to shift beliefs based on the previous question's point that decisions may be based on others receiving nothing given a failure, which I imagine would be a big factor in people's decisions as it was in mine.
